WEBVTT

00:04.665 --> 00:08.034
I can't tell you how much
I look forward to this.

00:08.036 --> 00:09.502
You look forward
to working out?

00:09.504 --> 00:12.672
Girl time. You know, talking
about shoes and shopping

00:12.674 --> 00:15.107
and anything other
than sports.

00:15.109 --> 00:17.376
I live in a man cave, you know.
(chuckles)

00:17.378 --> 00:19.045
I could use
a little more of that.

00:19.047 --> 00:20.680
The man, not the cave.
(chuckles)

00:20.682 --> 00:23.382
You know what you should
try? Speed dating.

00:23.384 --> 00:25.685
I should not try speed dating.
Yeah...

00:25.687 --> 00:27.587
Yeah, you should totally
try speed dating.

00:27.589 --> 00:30.323
It takes, like, an hour and you
come away with, like, 20 dates.

00:30.325 --> 00:31.136
No.

00:31.137 --> 00:32.909
I tell you what, you see
that food cart down there?

00:32.934 --> 00:34.127
Yeah.

00:34.128 --> 00:36.028
I will race you
to that food cart,

00:36.030 --> 00:38.664
and, if I win,
you go speed dating.

00:38.666 --> 00:40.399
What if I win?

00:40.401 --> 00:44.170
Um, I'll do family
dinners for a month.

00:44.172 --> 00:45.371
You ready?
On three.

00:45.373 --> 00:46.539
All right.
Prepare to lose.

00:46.541 --> 00:49.175
Three.
(chuckles) What?

00:51.812 --> 00:53.646
(laughing)

00:53.648 --> 00:55.481
DANNY:
<i>Best defensive end.</i>

00:55.483 --> 00:56.983
BAEZ:
<i>Reggie White.</i>

00:56.985 --> 00:58.384
No way.
Michael Strahan.

00:58.386 --> 00:59.619
The Minister of Defense.
That's all I'm gonna say.

00:59.621 --> 01:02.321
DANNY: <i>Oh, come on.</i>
<i>All right, best tight end.</i>

01:02.323 --> 01:03.746
BAEZ:
<i>Benny Allegretti. Hands down.</i>

01:03.747 --> 01:04.272
Who?

01:04.297 --> 01:05.890
I had a crush on
him in sixth grade.

01:06.861 --> 01:08.361
Oh, boy.

01:08.363 --> 01:10.530
What do we got?
Female,

01:10.532 --> 01:12.298
looks like mid-40s. No I.D.

01:12.300 --> 01:13.833
Just this business card
in her jacket.

01:13.835 --> 01:16.903
Dr. Alex Garland, St.
Benjamin's Medical Center.

01:16.905 --> 01:18.771
No purse, no belongings?
Nothing.

01:18.773 --> 01:19.972
Who called it in?

01:19.974 --> 01:21.140
Anonymous 911 call.

01:21.142 --> 01:22.608
Witnesses?
No.

01:22.610 --> 01:25.344
Who's the best defensive end
in NFL history, by the way?

01:25.346 --> 01:26.712
Jared Allen.

01:26.714 --> 01:29.348
Jared? Come on.
Beat it with that.

01:31.051 --> 01:33.119
What do you think?

01:33.121 --> 01:34.287
Robbery?

01:34.289 --> 01:35.755
Yeah,
maybe.

01:35.757 --> 01:37.723
But why would she be walking
along Newtown Creek?

01:37.725 --> 01:40.192
And in Christian Louboutins?
Say what?

01:40.194 --> 01:42.028
Those shoes cost
a thousand bucks, Reagan.

01:42.030 --> 01:45.097
Don't even try testing
my knowledge of high-end shoes.

01:45.966 --> 01:48.134
Hmm.

01:52.072 --> 01:54.006
Hey, Sarge.
We got one under

01:54.008 --> 01:56.208
for robbery and assault
in the first degree.

01:56.210 --> 01:57.455
Daniel Carson.
It's a lie.

01:57.456 --> 01:59.179
Oh, yeah. Just for the record, 
he's innocent.

01:59.204 --> 02:00.380
I'm sure.

02:00.381 --> 02:02.548
Man, I was gonna bring it all back.
This is all a big mistake--

02:02.550 --> 02:04.884
the witness I.D.,
the video surveillance.

02:04.886 --> 02:06.552
The evidence we found
in his possession.

02:06.577 --> 02:07.387
All right,

02:07.388 --> 02:09.822
Janko, start the paperwork.

02:09.824 --> 02:11.490
Reagan, you need to report

02:11.492 --> 02:13.826
to the chief of Ds' office
forthwith.

02:14.695 --> 02:16.729
Just me?

02:16.731 --> 02:18.431
That's what the boss said.

02:20.100 --> 02:21.867
You got it?
Uh-huh.

02:29.142 --> 02:30.676
(indistinct chatter)

02:30.678 --> 02:31.844
MAN:
We'll begin

02:31.846 --> 02:32.945
with the first gong.

02:32.947 --> 02:34.981
You will have five minutes
with each candidate.

02:34.983 --> 02:37.683
(gong clangs loudly)

02:40.520 --> 02:41.621
A musician?

02:41.623 --> 02:43.089
(English accent):
Yeah, drummer, actually.

02:43.091 --> 02:44.790
We're playing up in Rhinebeck
this weekend

02:44.792 --> 02:47.026
at the beer festival.
You should come and hang.

02:47.028 --> 02:48.260
It's gonna be epic.

02:48.262 --> 02:50.062
(gong clangs)

02:50.064 --> 02:51.597
My bonus was worth more
than my parents' house,

02:51.599 --> 02:52.732
you know what I'm saying?

02:52.734 --> 02:54.400
(gong clangs)

02:54.402 --> 02:55.401
Just one question.

02:55.403 --> 02:57.236
Um, do you like kids?

02:57.238 --> 02:58.270
What about
dogs? Uh,

02:58.272 --> 02:59.238
I have a Chowhuahua.

02:59.240 --> 03:00.840
Big head, little body,
falls a lot.

03:00.842 --> 03:01.842
That's a really nice dress.

03:01.843 --> 03:04.543
My mother helped me
pick this shirt out.

03:04.545 --> 03:05.645
You're really pretty.

03:05.647 --> 03:07.380
(gong clangs)

03:07.382 --> 03:10.349
Nice to meet you... Erin.

03:11.685 --> 03:13.052
First time
speed dating?

03:13.054 --> 03:15.254
And last.
It's, um...

03:15.256 --> 03:15.988
Weird?

03:15.990 --> 03:17.857
Yeah.
Yeah, I know.

03:17.859 --> 03:20.059
(phone vibrates)
Sorry, um...

03:20.061 --> 03:22.561
Hello. Just prepare
an order to produce

03:22.563 --> 03:23.929
and I'll sign it
when I get back.

03:23.931 --> 03:26.932
Okay. Sorry.

03:26.934 --> 03:29.602
(phone vibrates)
(groans)

03:29.604 --> 03:32.171
You know,
we only have five minutes.

03:32.173 --> 03:32.644
It's my office.

03:32.669 --> 03:33.807
Well, I'm sure they
can live without you for five...

03:33.808 --> 03:36.742
Hello.
Reschedule it

03:36.744 --> 03:38.611
around
the Saunder proffer.

03:38.613 --> 03:42.181
Okay. Sorry.

03:42.183 --> 03:43.549
No, you're not.

03:43.551 --> 03:44.917
Excuse me?

03:44.919 --> 03:46.352
If you were really sorry,

03:46.354 --> 03:48.454
you wouldn't be taking calls
from work that can wait.

03:48.456 --> 03:50.582
And how do you know
they can wait?

03:50.607 --> 03:52.025
When you have exactly

03:52.026 --> 03:54.026
five timed minutes
to talk to someone--

03:54.028 --> 03:55.995
someone who, by the way,
isn't enjoying this

03:55.997 --> 03:58.764
revolving door of "dates" any
more than you seem to be...

03:58.766 --> 04:00.213
For your information,
I'm not your date.

04:00.238 --> 04:01.401
Well, that's good,

04:01.402 --> 04:04.603
because if you were and you were
rude enough to take calls

04:04.605 --> 04:06.405
in the middle of a date, I'd have
been gone before the appetizers.

04:06.407 --> 04:09.008
Well, that would have been
perfectly fine with me

04:09.010 --> 04:10.409
because I certainly
would not want

04:10.411 --> 04:11.544
to waste my time
with a man

04:11.546 --> 04:15.147
who clearly has a problem
sharing attention.

04:23.056 --> 04:25.057
(exhales)

04:25.059 --> 04:27.226
(indistinct chatter)

04:29.730 --> 04:30.763
Hello.
Dr. Garland?

04:30.765 --> 04:31.797
Yeah.
Detectives Reagan and Baez.

04:31.799 --> 04:33.933
We have a few questions
for you.

04:33.935 --> 04:36.202
Okay. Well, I'm working,
so this needs to be quick.

04:36.204 --> 04:37.970
Uh, we're investigating
a homicide.

04:37.972 --> 04:41.207
The deceased had no I.D. on her
other than your business card.

04:41.209 --> 04:42.875
Well, I see hundreds
of patients a day.

04:42.877 --> 04:44.477
I give out hundreds of cards.
(chuckles)

04:44.479 --> 04:46.545
Can you just take a look
at this picture and see

04:46.547 --> 04:49.115
if you recognize her?

04:50.951 --> 04:52.618
Dr. Garland,
you know this woman?

04:54.821 --> 04:56.989
It's my wife.

04:58.000 --> 05:04.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

05:05.098 --> 05:07.032
Chief.

05:07.034 --> 05:10.236
Officer Reagan.

05:10.238 --> 05:11.637
Please sit.

05:16.977 --> 05:18.644
Yeah, we're ready.

05:18.646 --> 05:20.479
Okay.

05:22.082 --> 05:24.650
(sighs)

05:36.930 --> 05:39.899
(sighs)

05:39.901 --> 05:41.200
(door opens)

05:50.010 --> 05:52.378
You're not in trouble,
if that's what you're thinking.

05:52.380 --> 05:53.946
I don't know what to think.

05:56.416 --> 05:58.617
A ten-year-old
homicide case.

05:58.619 --> 06:00.052
Michelle Lowe.

06:00.054 --> 06:02.221
23 years old.

06:04.224 --> 06:06.125
Her mother thinks we got
the wrong guy.

06:06.127 --> 06:08.260
I want you to find out
if she's right.

06:09.896 --> 06:11.430
Why are you giving it to me?

06:11.432 --> 06:14.033
It's delicate.

06:14.035 --> 06:16.368
Needs to be under the radar.

06:17.938 --> 06:19.972
I need someone I can trust

06:19.974 --> 06:22.508
and someone who is capable.

06:24.578 --> 06:27.279
And I'm not asking;
it's an order.

